CH 1 FIRST APP

- Google maintains Android. Device manufacturers and carriers can modify Android deveices, and developers can build apps for free. 

- Beside Google Play, you can also launch the app through Amazon.

- First, you need to install the IDE,  ADT (Android Development Tools) and Android packages.

- You can configure the installed packages in the SDK from the Android SDK and AVD Manager (Android Virtual Device). 


- Main.xml layout has one ViewGroup with a single View inside it. (ViewGroup ex: LinearLayout)

- Layouts are defined in XML.



Installation Check List: 
- Install IDE
- Install the Android SDk
- Install the ADT plugin
- Install the SDK packages
- Configure the ADT
- Build your app






